hopobject.body: I'm self-employed eye magic Schadenfreude on my first evening in Hamburg. My taxi driver told me that the Elbphilharmonie, the brand-new concert hall, is massively over budget and not going to open on time. At first, I put it down to the usual problems of large-scale municipal works, but then I remembered I was in Germany, the origin of this word on loan to the English language, and a country renowned for prudence, efficiency and organisation. Double schadenfreude and, I must admit, rather a surprise. Completion date has now been put back to 2016.And surprise was to become a recurring feature of my stay in Hamburg. Carls, the restaurant where I dined on that first evening, is in a modern European office building.
